headline: STX Q1 Earnings Call: Cloud Demand and Technology Transition Drive Seagate’s Outperformance
summary: Data storage manufacturer Seagate (NASDAQ:STX) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 30.5% year on year to $2.16 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $2.4 billion was less impressive, coming in 0.6% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.90 per share was 9.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
